ut the straight trees and leave the rest." So the loggers turned all the straight trees into lumber and toothpicks and paper. And the crooked tree is still there, growing stronger and stranger every day.', 2201, 0), (8207, 'If you try and take a cat apart to see how it works, the first thing you have on your hands is a non-working cat.', 386, 0), (8208, 'Curran looked back at me. "Why is it you always attract creeps?""You tell me." Ha! Walked right into that one, yes, he did.', 762, 0), (8209, 'Death: "THERE ARE BETTER THINGS IN THE WORLD THAN ALCOHOL, ALBERT."Albert: "Oh, yes, sir. But alcohol sort of compensates for not getting them.', 195, 0), (8210, 'I''m calm," Rachel insisted. "Every time I''m around you, some monsters attack us. What''s to be nervous about?""Look," I said. "I''m sorry about the band room. I hope they didn''t kick you our or anything.""Nah. They asked me a lot of questions about you. I played dumb.""Was it hard?" Annabeth asked.', 80, 0), (8211, 'I didn''t fail the test, I just found 100 ways to do it wrong.', 1077, 0), (8212, 'How''re we getting to King''s Cross tomorrow, Dad?" asked Fred as they dug into a sumptuous pudding."The Ministry''s providing a couple of cars," said Mr. Weasley.Everyone looked up at him."Why?" said Percy curiously."It''s because of you, Perce," said George seriously. "And there''ll be little flags on the hoods, with HB on them-""-for Humongous Bighead," said Fred.', 28, 0), (8213, 'I cook with wine, sometimes I even add it to the food.', 2165, 0), (8214, 'I always pass on good advice. It is the only thing to do with it. It is never of any use to oneself.', 40, 0), (8215, 'I just can''t listen to any more Wagner, you know...I''m starting to get the urge to conquer Poland.', 281, 0), (8216, 'We''re so busy watching out for what''s just ahead of us that we don''t take time to enjoy where we are.', 983, 0), (8217, 'If you drink much from a bottle marked ''poison'' it is certain to disagree with you sooner or later.', 125