INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (9151, 'Of course, it is boring to read about boring thing, but it is better to read something that makes you yawn with boredom than something that will make you weep uncontrollably, pound your fists against the floor, and leave tearstains all over your pillowcase, sheets, and boomerang collection.', 59, 0), (9152, 'Often it does seem such a pity that Noah and his party did not miss the boat.', 286, 0), (9153, 'In the present case it is a little inaccurate to say I hate everything. I am strongly in favor of common sense, common honesty and common decency. This makes me forever ineligible to any public office of trust or profit in the Republic. But I do not repine, for I am a subject of it only by force of arms.', 411, 0), (9154, 'Don''t care for her tongue, do you? How strange. I find it one of my favorite parts.Bones to Gregor', 120, 0), (9155, 'The problem with doing nothing is that you never know when you''re finished.', 2299, 0), (9156, 'The road to creativity passes so close to the madhouse and often detours or ends there.', 2300, 0), (9157, 'I actually like how doctors talk. I like the sound of science. I like how words you don''t understand explain things you can''t understand.', 598, 0), (9158, 'Where I come from, we''re more about efficiency,'' he replies. ''A knife like this''ll skewer food, smear butter, and slit throats all at the same time.', 237, 0), (9159, 'NO PDA,school rules. And besides she''s my partner dickhead." said Alex.', 200, 0), (9160, 'Who knew that the devil had a factory where he made millions of fossils, which his minions distributed throughout the earth, in order to confuse my tiny brain?', 1870, 0), (9161, 'You know you have ADD when Look A chicken - T-shirt', 1490, 0), (9162, 'I think the very word stalking implies that you''re not supposed to like it. Otherwise, it would be called ''fluffy harmless observation time''.', 2301, 0), (9163, 'The French have a new president, the British will soon have a new P.M., and we envy them as we endure the endless wait for this small dim man to go back to Texas and resume his life.', 1205, 0), (9164, 'The leading cause of death among fashion models is falling through street grates.', 2223, 0), (9165, 'Death didn''t bother me much. Strong Christian and all that. Method of death did. Being eaten alive. One of my top three ways not to go out.', 142, 0), (9166, 'It seems that the young woman made some indelicate suggestion of a threesome...When I got there, Miss Nash was standing by the hot tub in a small bikini, pointing the business end of a SIG-Sauer P-226 at her fella and concerned members of the hotel staff, while dunking the scantily clad female''s head under the water and asking, "Who''s diving for clams now, bitch?', 762, 0), (9167, 'Either you go to America with Mrs. Van Hopper or you come home to Manderley with me.""Do you mean you want a secretary or something?""No, I''m asking you to marry me, you little fool.', 1214, 0), (9168, 'Why did Mother ask you to help me rescue Gelsi?" I asked Leif."She thought I could assist you in some way. Instead, I had tried to-""Kill me? You can join the ''I Want to Kill Yelena Guild.'' I hear they have sixmembers in good standing.Valek is president since he had wanted to kill me twice."--Yelena to Leif', 295, 0), (9169, 'Writing is the only profession where no one considers you ridiculous if you earn no money.', 1952, 0), (9170, 'The lack of money is the root of all evil.', 286, 0), (9171, 'Molly: So how do you think of Bryce Hamilton crowd so far? Boys hot enough for you?Bethany: I wouldn''t say hot. Most of them seem to have a normal body temperature.', 467, 0), (9172, 'I love Mickey Mouse more than any woman I have ever known.', 783, 0), (9173, 'And then Jack chopped down what was the world''s last beanstalk, adding murder and ecological terrorism to the theft, enticement, and trespass charges already mentioned, and all the giant''s children didn''t have a daddy anymore. But he got away with it and lived happily ever after, without so much as a guilty twinge about what he had done...which proves that you can be excused for just about anything if you are a hero, because no one asks inconvenient questions.', 195, 0), (9174, 'I spilled more times than a glass of milk on a roller coaster.', 180, 0), (9175, '[Myrnin to Claire about their costumes of Pierrot and Harlequin, respectively]"Don''t they teach you anything in your schools?".""Pity. I suppose that''s what comes of your main education flowing from Google.', 614, 0), (9176, 'I never hated a man enough to give him his diamonds back.', 2302, 0), (9177, 'The truth is, every son raised by a single mom is pretty much born married. I don''t know, but until your mom dies it seems like all the other women in your life can never be more than just your mistress.', 30, 0), (9178, 'Well, spit on my empty grave--if it ain''t the attack of the Disney princesses!', 729, 0), (9179, 'Just wait until he figures out I shut him out of his slut hut.', 762, 0), (9180, 'Sometimes when it looks like I''m deep in thought I''m just trying not to have a conversation with people.', 2024, 0), (9181, 'He smiled at that, and then his gaze shifted to a spot over my shoulder and it faded. ''These doubts wouldn’t have anything to do with the company you’re keeping of late, would they?''I didn’t get a chance to answer before the shop door was thrown open and a furious war mage stomped in. Pritkin spotted me and his eyes narrowed.''You shaved my legs?!''Mircea looked at me and folded his arms across his chest. I looked from one unhappy face to the other and suddenly remembered that I had somewhere else to be.', 2303, 0), (9182, 'Well enough,” I reply. “Remember, you’re drunk. And happy. You’re supposed to be lusting over your escort. Try smiling a little more.” like I’m lusting? This is me, lusting.” His lashes flutter at me. better.', 237, 0), (9183, 'Tell you what, you let me go, and I’ll ask you plenty of questions about your race. Until then, I’m slightly distracted with how this little vacation on the good ship Holy Sh*t is going to pan out for me.', 108, 0), (9184, 'Stop!" Narcissus got to his feet. "This is not right! This person is obviously not awesome, so he must be..." He struggled for the right words. It had probably been a long time since he''d talked about anything other than himself. "He must be tricking us." Apparently Narcissus wasn''t completely stupid.', 80, 0), (9185, 'Um...Mercer? Haven''t seen you in nearly a month. I was expecting something like, ''Oh Cross, love of my heart, fire of my loins, how I''ve longed--', 1524, 0), (9186, 'Everything is funny as long as it is happening to somebody else.', 1122, 0), (9187, 'I have noticed that the people who are late are often so much jollier than the people who have to wait for them.', 2304, 0), (9188, 'Look!" said Foaly, pointing with some urgency into the vast steel-gray gloom, "Someone who cares!', 958, 0), (9189, 'If you think I''m going to let six people risk their lives - !''''because it''s the first time for all of us,'' said Ron.''This is different, pretending to be me -''''Well, none of us really fancy it, Harry,'' said Fred earnestly. ''Imagine if something went wrong and we were stuck as specky, scrawny gits forever.''Harry did not smile. ''You can''t do it if I don''t cooperate, you need me to give you some hair.''''Well, that''s the plan scuppered,'' said George. ''Obviously there''s no chance at all of us getting a bit of your hair unless you cooperate.''''Yeah, thirteen of us against one bloke who''s not allowed to use magic; we''ve got no chance,'' said Fred.', 28, 0), (9190, 'I''ve heard that hard work never killed anyone, but I say why take the chance?', 1727, 0), (9191, 'I''m a werewolf trapped in a human body.""Well, yeah, that''s kind of the definition.""No, really. I''m trapped.""Oh? When was the last time you shape-shifted?""That''s just it - I''ve never shape-shifted.""So you''re not really a werewolf.""Not yet. But I was meant to be one, I just know it. How do I get a werewolf to attack me?"Stand in the middle of a forest under a full moon with a raw steak tied to your face, holding a sign that says, ''Eat me; I''m stupid''?', 2305, 0), (9192, 'I really should come with a warning label.', 1443, 0), (9193, 'I need to look like an idiot at least twice a day to keep myself humble. ', 1105, 0), (9194, 'And Nate? You kiss like a slobbering dog, you have bad breath, and you wouldn''t know how to punch the right buttons on a girl if we came with manuals. Happy Thanksgiving, Jackass.', 2306, 0), (9195, 'Frank didn’t drop you on purpose,” she said. “He’s not like that. He’s just a little clumsy sometimes.”“Oops,” Leo said, in his best Frank Zhang voice. “Dropped Leo into a squad of enemy soldiers. Dang it!', 80, 0), (9196, 'Any idiot can put up a website.', 376, 0), (9197, 'Okay, seriously, I dont know if this is true or not, but I heard people who use profanity are trying to compensate for their lack of you know... size" -Tuck', 200, 0), (9198, 'He who can, does. He who cannot, teaches. ', 266, 0), (9199, 'Call me sentimental, but there''s no-one in the world that I''d like to see get dysentery more than you', 158, 0), (9200, 'When I''m out of politics I''m going to run a business, it''ll be called rent-a-spine', 1945, 0);
